Classification rules:
- Self-signed certs (subject matches issuer) on non-production services are low risk, strategy: self-signed-regenerate
- CA-issued PEM certs (IPA/internal CA) are medium risk, strategy: ipa-certmonger-renew
- CA-issued certs in Java keystores are critical due to required service restart, strategy: ipa-issue-keytool-import
- Certs with fewer days remaining should have lower recommended_order (renew first)
- If a service name contains "api" or "prod", increase risk one level
- Java keystore renewals always require chatops-war-room approval
- PEM CA-issued renewals require aap-workflow approval
- Self-signed renewals require no approval
